n Quebec is based on the inevitabilities of the class antagonisms set up by capitalism. The authors believe that it is only through such Marxist theory and practice that a way can be found for Canada to escape at last from imperialist exploitation and that a way can be found to shape a socialist future for the whole country.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aSocial classeszCanada. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economic Conditions.2bisacsh1 aBourque, Gilles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBronson, H.E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoward, Roger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Leo A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaurin-Frenette, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLipton, Charles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorris, R.B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNaylor, R.T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRyerson, Stanley B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aScott, Jack, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTeeple, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTeeple, Gary, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148758389740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487583897423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487583897.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_